 Sure! Here is a Python function that sorts a list of elements using the comb sort algorithm:
```
def comb_sort(list):
    n = len(list)
    for i in range(n // 2 - 1):
        for j in range(i, n - i - 1):
            if list[j] > list[j + 1]:
                list[j], list[j + 1] = list[j + 1], list[j]
    return list
```
Note: This is a basic implementation of the comb sort algorithm, which has a time complexity of O(n log n) on average.

 Sure! Here is a Python function that sorts a list of elements using the comb sort algorithm:
```
def comb_sort(list):
    n = len(list)
    for i in range(n//2 - 1, -1, -1):
        for j in range(i, n):
            if list[j] < list[j+1]:
                list.insert(i, list[j])
                list.insert(j+1, list[j+1])
    return list
```
Note: This is a basic implementation of the comb sort algorithm, which has a time complexity of O(n^2). For larger lists, other sorting algorithms may be more efficient.

